Roman Numerals

It is quite simple. Change an Arabic number to a combination of letters from the Latin alphabet.

Symbols:
I   1
V   5
X   10
L   50
C   100
D   500
M   1000

Usage:
roman.fromNumber(1234) should give MCCXXXIV.
There are some numbers which are not allowed, ex.: negative numbers and numbers greater than 3999.
